    "excerpt": "Pelican Lake near Breezy Point pairs big water with resort amenities, golf, and marinas. Here is what buyers should know in 2026.",
    "body": "<p>Pelican Lake near Breezy Point sits in the Brainerd Lakes region and pairs a large, open lake with the amenities of an established resort community. At roughly 8,300 acres, it offers real boating and fishing water, and the surrounding Breezy Point and Pequot Lakes area layers in golf, marinas, dining, and services. For buyers who want an active resort-style lake rather than a remote cabin, Pelican Lake is a strong 2026 candidate.</p><h2>The resort-community appeal</h2><p>What sets this area apart is the built-in lifestyle around the water. Breezy Point Resort anchors a community with golf courses, a marina, and year-round events, so ownership here comes with amenities on tap. That resort backbone also supports a rental market, which some buyers use to offset carrying costs, subject to local rules.</p><ul><li>Large open lake with strong boating and multi-species fishing</li><li>Golf, marinas, and dining in the Breezy Point and Pequot Lakes area</li><li>Established resort community with year-round activity</li><li>Rental potential in some areas, if allowed and managed well</li></ul><p>Weigh Pelican against other Brainerd-area lakes using our <a href='/compare-lakes'>compare lakes</a> tool to see where it lands on price and amenities.</p><h2>Shoreline and property types</h2><p>Pelican Lake offers a range from traditional lakefront cabins to condo and townhome options within resort developments, which is unusual for a Minnesota lake. That variety means you can buy true detached lakefront or a lower-maintenance association property with shared access. Each path has different costs and responsibilities.</p><ul><li>Detached lakefront homes offer privacy and full control</li><li>Condos and townhomes offer lower maintenance and shared amenities</li><li>Association dues and rules apply to shared-access properties</li><li>Confirm bottom type and dock rights on any lakefront lot</li></ul><p>Decide which ownership style fits you, then run the <a href='/lake-buyer-checklist'>lake buyer checklist</a> against the specific property.</p><h2>Prices and what to expect</h2><p>Pricing spans a wide band because the property types do. Association condos provide the most affordable entry to the area, while prime detached lakefront with good frontage sits well above that. Amenities, view, and proximity to the resort core all move price.</p><ul><li>Association properties are the affordable entry point</li><li>Detached lakefront commands a clear premium</li><li>Deep, sandy frontage adds value on true lakefront</li><li>Factor association dues into your monthly budget</li></ul><p>Use the <a href='/lake-mortgage-calculator'>lake mortgage calculator</a> to compare a lakefront home's carrying cost against a condo with dues before you decide.</p><h2>Due diligence in the resort area</h2><p>For association properties, read the governing documents carefully: dues, rental rules, reserve funds, and any special assessments. For detached lakefront, the usual well, septic, and shoreland checks apply. If rental income is part of your plan, confirm what local ordinances and any association allow before you count on it.</p><ul><li>Review association budgets, reserves, and rental rules if buying a condo</li><li>Order septic and well inspections on detached lakefront</li><li>Confirm short-term rental rules if income is part of your plan</li><li>Check dock rights and shoreline permits</li></ul><h2>Lifestyle and who Pelican Lake suits</h2><p>Pelican Lake near Breezy Point is built for buyers who want their lake time active and social rather than remote and quiet. Golf, marinas, dining, and a busy summer calendar mean there is always something to do, and the resort backbone makes the area welcoming to newcomers who do not already have a cabin network. Families, golfers, and buyers who like amenities on tap gravitate here. If you crave solitude, a quieter Brainerd-area lake may fit better, but for an amenity-rich lake life, Pelican is hard to beat.</p><ul><li>Active, social lake life with golf and marina access</li><li>Welcoming to newcomers thanks to the resort community</li><li>Good fit for families and amenity-focused buyers</li><li>Quieter lakes may suit those who want solitude instead</li></ul><p>Not sure this is your speed? The <a href='/find-your-lake'>find your lake</a> quiz can match your priorities to the right kind of lake before you tour.</p><p>A local agent can tell you which developments and shoreline stretches hold value and which come with surprises. When you are ready, <a href='/buy'>get matched with a local agent — it's free</a>, and shop the Pelican Lake and Breezy Point area with someone who knows the community inside out.</p>"
