    "excerpt": "Pokegama Lake near Grand Rapids offers deep clear water and in-town convenience. Here is what buyers should know before shopping in 2026.",
    "body": "<p>Pokegama Lake sits right beside Grand Rapids in Itasca County, giving buyers a rare combination of deep, clear water and immediate access to a full-service town. At roughly 6,600 acres with depths that support cool-water fish and excellent clarity, Pokegama is one of the more desirable lakes in the region. Add Grand Rapids with its hospital, shopping, and airport, and you have a lake that works for full-time living, not just summers. Here is how to buy on Pokegama in 2026.</p><h2>What makes Pokegama stand out</h2><p>Depth and clarity are the headline. Pokegama runs deep, which keeps the water clear and supports a fishery including walleye, bass, and even cisco. That clarity, combined with being minutes from Grand Rapids, makes it a premium lake in the area and a favorite for year-round residents who want water quality without remoteness.</p><ul><li>Deep, clear water with strong clarity and a diverse fishery</li><li>Minutes from Grand Rapids services, healthcare, and an airport</li><li>Multiple connected bays offering varied frontage</li><li>Popular for full-time and four-season living</li></ul><p>Compare Pokegama against other Itasca-area lakes with our <a href='/compare-lakes'>compare lakes</a> tool to see how its water quality and price line up.</p><h2>Shoreline and neighborhoods</h2><p>Pokegama has several bays and a varied shoreline, from rock and gravel to sandier stretches. Its depth means good water off many docks, a plus for boating and swimming. Some frontage is close enough to town for near-urban convenience, while other stretches feel more secluded. Confirm bottom type and depth at the specific lot rather than assuming.</p><ul><li>Depth off the dock is often good, benefiting boating and swimming</li><li>Bottom type ranges from rock to sand by location</li><li>Some lots offer near-town convenience, others more seclusion</li><li>Confirm sewer/water versus well and septic by parcel</li></ul><p>Bring our <a href='/lake-buyer-checklist'>lake buyer checklist</a> to verify these details in person at every showing.</p><h2>Prices and value</h2><p>As one of the premier lakes near Grand Rapids, Pokegama tends to price above surrounding lakes, and clear-water frontage with a four-season home sits at the top of the local range. The premium reflects real water quality and year-round livability, which supports resale. Buyers seeking value sometimes trade a bit of depth for a lower entry on nearby lakes, but many decide Pokegama is worth it.</p><ul><li>Premium pricing reflects depth, clarity, and town access</li><li>Four-season homes with good frontage command the top range</li><li>Water quality supports resale demand</li><li>Nearby lakes offer lower entry if budget is tight</li></ul><p>Set your budget with the <a href='/lake-mortgage-calculator'>lake mortgage calculator</a> before touring so you can act on the right listing.</p><h2>Due diligence on Pokegama</h2><p>Confirm whether a given lot is on municipal services or well and septic, since both exist around this lake. For deeper, older homes, check the condition of shoreline structures and any seawalls given the lake's size and wave action. Verify shoreland setbacks before planning additions, as Itasca County enforces them.</p><ul><li>Confirm sewer/water status or order septic and well inspections</li><li>Check seawall and shoreline condition for ice and wave damage</li><li>Verify shoreland setbacks before planning any additions</li><li>Ask for permits on docks, lifts, and riprap</li></ul><h2>Lifestyle and year-round appeal</h2><p>Pokegama is a lake people live on, not just visit. The depth and clarity make for excellent swimming and boating in summer, while the fishery keeps anglers engaged from ice-out through the winter hardwater season. Being minutes from Grand Rapids means you can enjoy true lake life without sacrificing the conveniences of a real town, from the hospital to the grocery store to the airport. That combination is what pushes Pokegama to the top of the local market and keeps four-season homes in steady demand.</p><ul><li>Deep, clear water ideal for swimming and boating</li><li>Year-round fishing including a strong winter season</li><li>Town conveniences minutes from the shore</li><li>Steady demand for four-season homes</li></ul><p>If four-season livability drives your search, the <a href='/find-your-lake'>find your lake</a> quiz can confirm Pokegama fits how you plan to use the water before you drive up.</p><p>A local agent who knows Pokegama's bays can point you to the frontage that matches your budget and use. When you are ready, <a href='/buy'>get matched with a local agent — it's free</a>, and shop this premier Grand Rapids lake with an expert.</p>"
